m and breaks new ground with its multilingual approach across languages and nations. The book will appeal to scholars working within different linguistic traditions interested in questions relating to all aspects of standardisation and prescriptivism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexGrammarxHistory. 0aSpace and time in languagexHistory. 0aStandard languagexHistory. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aLanguage planning.  aLinguistic ideologies.  aLinguistic ideology.  aLinguistic prescriptivism.  aLinguistic standardisation.  aPrescriptivism.  aSociolinguistics.  aStandardisation.  aTraditional language.1 aAmeka, Felix K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAyres-Bennett, Wendy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanhold, Dominik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarasa, Sandra Nekesa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarros, Rita Queiroz de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCandel, Danielle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChapman, Don, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoulmas, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuijff, Pieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGill, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGjurkova, Aleksandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaunisto, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlöter, Henning, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLochtman, Katja, econtribut